The paper deals with handwriting verification using deep learning and proposes a method to generate explanations for the confidence provided by the convolutional neural network. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves feature learning and probabilistic graphical models, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a dataset for evaluation, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
